OL,7,FHowever, judges at the Court of Appeal
OL,8,Foverturned this ruling the following
OL,9,Fmonth.
OL,11,FFollowing a review by retired civil
OL,12,Fservant Paul Rimmer, which concluded
OL,13,Fthe government may have "inadvertently
OL,14,Fadded more value to the dataset" by
OL,15,Fseeking the unprecedented
OL,16,Fsuperinjunction, and that as the
OL,17,Fdefacto government in Afghanistan the
OL,18,FTaliban would already have access to
OL,19,Fsignifficant information on these
OL,20,Findividuals - the MoD agreed on July 4
OL,21,Fthat the order could be lifted.
